net.hudup.core.data

Class InternalRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.InternalRecord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, TextParsable

    public class InternalRecord
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, Cloneable, TextParsable
    This class represents a single-value record of a unit in framework database. Note, unit represents a CSV file, database table, Excel sheet, etc. Unit is used to store object such as user profile, item profile, rating matrix, etc. As a convention, this class is called internal record which opposite to external record represented by ExternalRecord. It includes three parts as follows:
    • Unit name referred by public variable unit.
    • Attribute name (like field name in database table) referred by public variable attribute.
    • Value of such attribute name referred by public variable value.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
